Found this in my garden, growing near potatoes, shallots, clover, and weeds. Small and yellow, about the size of a golf ball. There are like horizontal ridges around the stalk where there is just a tint of color. I don’t know the name for that. It’s not exactly the ring from veil. Reticulum? We got almost 4 inches of rain in 1 week. Since then it’s been warm and dry for 3 days and I found this growing in dry compost. There’s hay mulch around, but this was definitely growing in the soil. It wasn’t there yesterday. I didn’t want to pick it to look at the gills until it’s grown a bit more and opened up. If it grows more and opens up. I’ll take another look tomorrow.
EDIT, Day 2:
The mushroom has gotten larger, two more sprouted beneath it. Color has changed a bit. The cap has lost the yellow/green tint. Now more off-white and tan. I cut the stem open. There were yellow parts inside, and the stem isn’t hollow. It has a pleasant sweet smell. The gills are gray/lilac/rusty brown. I think the rusty brown part is from the spore. Brought it inside and I put the cap on a piece of paper to get a spore print. Should have one tomorrow. FWIW, the mushroom sprouted about 10 feet from a hazelnut shrub. Close enough for the roots to reach it. Could be growing in association with that hazel.
EDIT, Day 3
The spore is black. Maybe very dark brown or very dark purple.
